        Note over User,Reconciler: Flow 1: Model Registry Instance Provisioning
        User->>K8sAPI: Create ModelRegistry CR<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount/User token
        K8sAPI->>Webhook: Mutate + Validate CR<br/>HTTPS/9443 TLS (serving cert)<br/>Auth: k8s API server cert
        Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Admission Response
        K8sAPI->>Reconciler: Watch event (CR created)<br/>TLS, ServiceAccount token
        Reconciler->>K8sAPI: Create Deployment, Service,<br/>Route, NetworkPolicy, RBAC<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    end

    participant Client as External Client
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant OAuth as oauth-proxy sidecar<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant REST as rest-container<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant DB as PostgreSQL/MySQL<br/>5432/3306 TCP

    rect rgb(255, 245, 230)
        Note over Client,DB: Flow 2: Model Registry REST API Access (OAuth-protected)
        Client->>Router: REST API Request<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS (edge)
        Router->>OAuth: Forward (reencrypt)<br/>HTTPS/8443 TLS
        OAuth->>K8sAPI: TokenReview<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
        K8sAPI-->>OAuth: Token Valid
        OAuth->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>(get services/{name})<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS
        K8sAPI-->>OAuth: Authorized
        OAuth->>REST: Proxy request<br/>HTTP/8080 plaintext (localhost)
        REST->>DB: Query ML Metadata<br/>TCP 5432/3306<br/>Configurable SSL<br/>Auth: DB credentials
        DB-->>REST: Query Results
        REST-->>OAuth: Response
        OAuth-->>Router: HTTPS Response
        Router-->>Client: JSON Response
    end

    participant CatalogInit as catalog-data-init<br/>(Init Container)
    participant CatalogOAuth as catalog oauth-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Catalog as model-catalog<br/>8080/TCP HTTP

    rect rgb(230, 255, 230)
        Note over Client,Catalog: Flow 3: Model Catalog Data Flow
        CatalogInit->>Catalog: Load default catalog data<br/>File I/O (shared volume)
        Note over Catalog: ConfigMap volume<br/>(catalog sources)
        Client->>Router: Catalog API Request<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS
        Router->>CatalogOAuth: Forward (reencrypt)<br/>HTTPS/8443 TLS
        CatalogOAuth->>Catalog: Proxy request<br/>HTTP/8080 plaintext (localhost)
        Catalog-->>CatalogOAuth: Response
